@@TJvXPCustomComponent
Summary
  Base class for XP style components.
Description
  Derive from TJvXPCustomComponent when you want to create a non-visual component that is part of the
  XP style component hierarchy.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomControl
Summary
  Base class for XP style controls.
Description
  Derive from TJvXPCustomControl when you want to create a visual control that has the basic properties
  and events of the XP style controls. Do not create instances of TJvXPCustomControl.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomControl.DrawState
Summary
  Describes the current state of the control.
Description
  Use DrawState to determine or change the current state of the control. DrawState is used to modify
  the visual appearance of the control.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomControl.IsLocked
Summary
  Determines if the control is being updated.
Description
  IsLocked is true when a call to BeginUpdate has been made without a corresponding call to EndUpdate.
  When IsLocked is true, the control is not redrawn. Use IsLocked to make multiple updates to the
  visual appearance of the control without redrawing it between each change.
See Also
  BeginUpdate, EndUpdate

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomControl.IsSibling
Summary
  Determines if the currently selected control is a sibling of this control.
Description
  \Read IsSibling to determine if the currently focused control is also a TJvXPCustomControl

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomControl.ModalResult
Summary
  Determines whether and how the control closes its (modal) parent form.
Description
  Setting the TJvXPCustomControl's ModalResult property is an easy way to make clicking the control
  close a modal form. When a TJvXPCustomControl is clicked, the ModalResult property of its parent form
  is set to the same value as the TJvXPCustomControl's ModalResult property.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomControl.OnMouseEnter
Summary
  Occurs when the mouse pointer moves over the control.
Description
  Write an OnMouseEnter event handler to take specific action when the user moves the mouse over the
  control.
See Also
  TJvXPCustomControl.OnMouseLeave

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomControl.OnMouseLeave
Summary
  Occurs when the mouse pointer moves off the control.
Description
  Write an OnMouseLeave event handler to take specific action when the user moves the mouse off the
  control. For example, you can use this event to undo changes that were made in an OnMouseEnter event
  handler.
See Also
  TJvXPCustomControl.OnMouseEnter

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomStyleControl
Summary
  Base class for controls that can have their appearance modified by a style manager.
Description
  TJvXPCustomStyleControl introduces the Style and StyleManager property. These properties allows
  centralized control over the look and feel of controls.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomStyleControl.Style
Summary
  Determines the style of the control.
Description
  Use Style to set a visual style for the control.
See Also
  TJvXPCustomStyleControl.StyleManager

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomStyleControl.StyleManager
Summary
  Sets the style manager responsible for drawing the control.
Description
  Set StyleManager to point to a TJvXPStyleManager instance on your form. If you set the same style
  manager for all TJvXPCustomControls on the form, you can control the style of all controls from one
  central point
See Also
  TJvXPCustomStyleControl.Style

