@@TJvXPGradient
Summary
  Defines properties for drawing an image gradient.
Description
  TJvXPGradient defines properties for drawing a gradient image. The gradient is available through the
  Bitmap variable.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPGradient.Bitmap
Summary
  Contains a gradient image.
Description
  Use bitmap to access the gradient created by the class based on its property settings. For example,
  the bitmap can be used as the background of an XP style control.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPGradient.Colors
Summary
  Defines the number of colors in the gradient.
Description
  Use Colors to define the number of color shifts the gradient contains. The minimum value for Colors
  is 2 and the maximum value is 255.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPGradient.Dithered
Summary
  Determines how the gradient is color matched.
Description
  Use dithered to determine how the gradient is color matched. When dithered is true, a color

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPGradient.Enabled
Summary
  Defines if the gradient is drawn in an enabled or disabled style.
Description
  Use Enabled to control the general visual appearance of the gradient. When Enabled is true, the
  gradient is more "alive" than when disabled.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPGradient.EndColor
Summary
  Determines the end color of the gradient.
Description
  Use EndColor to \read and change the end color of the gradient. The gradient is created as a color
  starting with StartColor and shifting towards EndColor using the number of color bands determined by
  Colors.
See Also
  TJvXPGradient.Colors, TJvXPGradient.StartColor, TJvXPGradient.Style

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPGradient.RecreateBands
Summary
  Recreates the gradient.
Description
  Call RecreateBands to recreate the gradient.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPGradient.StartColor
Summary
  Determines the start color of the gradient.
Description
  Use StartColor to \read and change the start color of the gradient. The gradient is created as a
  color starting with StartColor and shifting towards EndColor using the number of color bands
  determined by Colors.
See Also
  TJvXPGradient.Colors, TJvXPGradient.EndColor, TJvXPGradient.Style

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPGradient.Style
Summary
  Defines the origin of the gradient.
Description
  Use Style to change the origin of the gradient. Style determines where the gradient's starts drawing
  with its StartColor.
See Also
  TJvXPGradient.Colors, TJvXPGradient.EndColor, TJvXPGradient.StartColor

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPGradientColors
